The paper deals with the intersection graphs of paths on a rectangular grid, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The specific shapes considered in the paper are L-shaped paths, which are commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of testing for membership in certain graph classes, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions characterizations and recognition algorithms for special subclasses of graphs, which could fall under the category of algorithmic graph theory (cs.GT).
